Updated ViewModel structure. Connections is a JSON array, with objects, each of which have their own course objects. Instead of making an array, utilizes "input"/"output" properties of these objects. PROGRESS: Code draws green circles for courses taken, red circles for those not taken and not required, gray circles for those not taken and required. Note that the ViewModel_Test.json being imported is AN EXAMPLE CONFIGURATION. However, VM_to_Model.js is written to accommodate tagged booleans, so this should be easily scalable.
Initial Noticed Bugs: 1. Dragging the node is necessary to position the text and make connections appear. No idea why this is happening, might be something to do with when drag is executed. 2. Having hard time figuring out how to scale arrows down–right now, the arrowhead is hidden behind the node, making it just look like an undirected graph. 3. Spacing problem. How do we get this to look nice? Also, consider implementing the "drag and don't touch" example in the D3 wiki. 4. In general, we're going to run out of space in placing all the nodes. 5. How do we get dragging behavior from one panel (not taken not required courses) to the main interface?
